A truck was burnt at Maepa village in Atok outside Burgersfort
after community went on the rampage, and barricaded the R37 with rocks and
burning tyres. The residents began pelting passing motor vehicles with stones. Police spokesperson Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said the total damage
caused is estimated to be millions of rands. Ngoepe also said at this stage, no incidents of injuries or
fatalities were reported. “Cases of malicious damage to property and public violence were
opened. The suspects involved in these incidents are still unknown and there is
no arrest,” Ngoepe said. Ngoepe urged anyone who can assist the police with information
that can lead to the arrest of the suspects in this matter, to contact
Brigadier James Espach at 082 576 0743 or the Crime Stop number at 0860010111. 